OL,3,CHolocaust survivors urge Nigel Farage
OL,4,Cto apologise for alleged racist abuse
OL,6,FHe has previously said of the claims
OL,7,Fthat what could have been considered
OL,8,F"banter in a playground" could be
OL,9,Finterpreted differently in "the modern
OL,10,Flight of day in some sort of way".
OL,12,FNow, 11 signatories, some of whom have
OL,13,Fsurvived Nazi death camps, have said
OL,14,Fin a letter that they "understand the
OL,15,Fdanger of hateful words", calling on
OL,16,Fthe Clacton MP to admit whether he
OL,17,Fsaid them or if he is accusing those
OL,18,Fwho say he did of lying.
